Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As times change, difficult\Ncases increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.74,0:00:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's stage is a treasure hunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.75,0:00:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will we find treasure of the heart?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.41,0:00:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the\Nsingle truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.30,0:00:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.83,0:01:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective League Survival Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Professor!\NIs this map real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it certainly is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, then there\Nreally is treasure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have\Nto find out, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.79,0:02:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will find that treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.79,0:02:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me three!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.67,0:02:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you get\Nthat phony map anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd just lie anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find out for yourself\Nwhen you get to the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the end, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too old for treasure hunts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where we are, at Skull Tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you need to make\Nyour way to London Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.75,0:03:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to do\Nsome fishing here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so have fun, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, I'm not a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.22,0:03:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.27,0:03:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think the treasure is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know\Nif there really is treasure--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course there is! Right, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Diamonds, or jewels,\Nor maybe even buried gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! That'd be awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.20,0:03:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:52.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Skull Tree
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:54.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,London Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.22,0:04:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried it might fall down
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since it's called\Nthe London Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, bridges like this\Nalways break in the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.49,0:04:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was the Professor thinking,\Nsending us out here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.50,0:04:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now how do we get back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:40.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,London Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:43.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil's Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My compass doesn't\Nseem to work out here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.72,0:04:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd he hafta hide the\Ntreasure in these mountains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a mystery geek...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.10,0:04:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break! The map says there's\Nfive cedar trees but there's only four here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.86,0:05:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really the place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about bad luck--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.82,0:05:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he died in an accident\Njust after burying the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! The treasure's at stake here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer when I ask you something!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.58,0:05:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's dangerous, Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should put cigarettes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.88,0:05:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't want\Nto start a forest fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the Junior Detective League!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? These maps look a lot alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What're you lookin' at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.61,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.90,0:05:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys don't seem like hikers!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have a shovel,\Nbut they're wearing suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what exactly is that map?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we're right here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Yeah, I think so,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the compass isn't working...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan! There's only four cedar trees.\NIs this the right place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move for a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! This is the fifth cedar tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to tell because\Nit was chopped down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See how these annual\Nrings are pointing out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This side got a lot more\Nsunlight so it grew better!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that way's south?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.03,0:06:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.49,0:06:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So which path do we take?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Devil's Hand - Enter\Nthrough the narrow path."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Devil's Hand" is your left hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that narrows it\Ndown to the two on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says,\N"Enter through the narrow path,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we take the narrowest\Npath on the very left!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:06:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so smart, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the "Devil's Hand"\Nis your left hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's your right hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Angel's Hand," of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so simple-minded...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do those kids have that map?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.74,0:07:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kid sure is smart, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.74,0:07:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry before\Nthey beat us to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.66,0:07:18.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil's Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:20.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Speckled Band
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.50,0:07:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two guys seemed fishy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're definitely looking\Nfor the same treasure as us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they did mention treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help, I'm drowning! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.45,0:08:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.05,0:08:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was a goner!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.26,0:08:14.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Speckled Band
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:15.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,River Dove
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:17.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Walton's Shore
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the best camping\Nmatches will light when they get wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.44,0:08:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it. I was hoping\Nwe could dry our clothes off...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.07,0:08:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take the top\Noff the flashlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remove the reflector,\Nand put a match in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I just point it at the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and collect the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a good camping match,\Nbut it's still dripping wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.42,0:08:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure\Nit's even usable now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:08:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:08:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got "old lady wisdom"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you at least\Ncall it survival knowledge?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:14.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Speckled Band
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:16.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Double-Head Arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you! Which way is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.33,0:09:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like something's\Nwritten on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.71,0:09:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to read, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we go east?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, then which way is east?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.30,0:09:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.93,0:09:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was too dangerous\Nfor them to go alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extinguish complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extinguish confirmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.86,0:09:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we can really\Nmake it to the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:09:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do we go from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna\Nclimb up that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.37,0:10:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're right here,\Nso if we go around like this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll make it to\Nour next destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.46,0:10:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:17.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Walton's Shore
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:18.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandit's Balance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.14,0:10:24.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Bandit's Balance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.77,0:10:26.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Weissmuller's Gorge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9.9...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:27.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Weissmuller's Gorge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.24,0:11:29.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Double-Head Arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.30,0:11:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only cut recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.51,0:11:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it was chopped\Nwith something sharp...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.93,0:11:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But not a knife or a blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.80,0:11:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a shovel or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A shovel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! Those two were here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:12:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think it says?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.96,0:12:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like some sort of code,\Nbut it's unreadable...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.67,0:12:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we put paper on it\Nand rub a pencil over it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.13,0:12:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,won't the letters come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.97,0:12:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.51,0:12:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't bring\Nany paper or pencils...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.81,0:12:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.73,0:12:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a felt-tip\Npen for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd work!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.77,0:12:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This would?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, what Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0} suggested!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.57,0:12:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.19,0:12:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.49,0:12:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First I pour canteen water on the sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I rub dirt into the writing,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.58,0:12:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when I wipe it away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.71,0:12:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dirt stays in the carved writing,\Nmaking it readable!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.59,0:12:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The sun's hand shows\Nthe time and way. Go east!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.51,0:12:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, which way is east?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.59,0:12:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Good question...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No tree trunks this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.93,0:13:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun's hand? Go east?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.44,0:13:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.19,0:13:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this'll show\Nus which way is which!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you point the\Nhour hand at the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.66,0:13:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,south is halfway\Nbetween it and the twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.87,0:13:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So east is ninety degrees to the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.00,0:13:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.96,0:13:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way is east!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.29,0:13:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\N"Old lady wisdom - part two"!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.55,0:13:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop saying that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.47,0:13:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:37.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tree of Bosporus
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.81,0:13:44.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Chieftain's Home
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.48,0:13:53.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Bear and Little Bear Hill
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Walk from where the sky water\Nand stones point. Five."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you\Nthink the "sky water" is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.42,0:14:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that too simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five stone pillars...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If these are the stones, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.60,0:14:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta! Gimme a lift!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big idea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.19,0:14:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pillars form a W!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W... West... That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.03,0:14:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what does "sky water" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.53,0:14:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NDid you figure anything out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm wondering if it's five\Npaces west of the middle pillar...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.71,0:14:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.38,0:14:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan!\NThere's nothing here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's not a W,\Nthen maybe an M...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.14,0:15:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or it could be a B!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.18,0:15:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's the sky water--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mitsuhiko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.23,0:15:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tripped over a tree
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.95,0:15:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hit my head on that stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A tree and a stone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.25,0:15:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't appear to have\Nbeen moved for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.96,0:15:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.26,0:15:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this shape be--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Big Dipper,\Nmade out of logs and stones!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.47,0:15:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.73,0:15:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's shaped like a ladle,\Nhence the "sky water"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.60,0:15:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.82,0:15:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! Those pillars are\Nthe Cassiopeia constellation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:16:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\Nthe sky water and the stones
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.12,0:16:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,point to the North Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The North Star is located\Nabout five times the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.54,0:16:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,between the two end stars\Nof the Big Dipper!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.04,0:16:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's also located off\Nof Cassiopeia's central star,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.13,0:16:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about five times the distance\Nbetween each of its stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sneaky Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! There's a\Nrock with writing on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.27,0:16:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured as such!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.86,0:16:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Polaris is the North Star,\Nhence the P!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it! This is\Ndefinitely the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, five paces!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.91,0:16:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One! Two! Three! Four!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.29,0:16:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.01,0:16:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.52,0:17:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Is this--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.32,0:17:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and open it, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.74,0:17:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could these jewels actually be--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.37,0:17:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can have all\Nthe eel dishes in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.88,0:17:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! And I'll--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.59,0:17:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to interrupt...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.21,0:17:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I'll be taking that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.68,0:17:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These guys are jewel thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.93,0:17:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.98,0:17:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be tryin' to play hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.82,0:18:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man down there\Nsaid to give you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he tripped and hit his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean like Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not funny! It really hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.10,0:18:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it-- our real treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.19,0:18:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.86,0:18:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me this is the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.28,0:18:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This single scrap of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.54,0:18:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What does it say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:19:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The treasure is everything\Nyou experienced to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.38,0:19:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might have\Nfallen into the river,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.01,0:19:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,started a fire, caught fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.47,0:19:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and worked with your\Nfriends to arrive here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.43,0:19:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of those experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might not understand this now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but someday it will\Nbe an obvious treasure--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.86,0:19:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and probably worth a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.44,0:19:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If possible, please pass this\Nadventure on to your successors!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.91,0:19:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.25,0:19:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like... Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku, Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.93,0:19:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find out for yourself\Nwhen you get to the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.27,0:20:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad wrote this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could possibly duplicate\Nthat peculiar K of his?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.20,0:20:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've noticed from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.95,0:20:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The summit across the\Nriver we were camping on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.12,0:20:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the place we were looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.29,0:20:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected to\Nsee the Professor's camp
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.59,0:20:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the top of that tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.97,0:20:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even though\Nit wasn't very far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.64,0:20:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,getting there was pretty hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.23,0:20:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon hearing the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.73,0:20:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the professor immediately\Ncalled the police
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.65,0:20:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the jewel thieves were arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.02,0:20:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They decided to question\Nus the following day
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.57,0:20:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we got to go for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.03,0:20:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called it a stupid\Ntreasure hunt at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.20,0:21:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but adventures\Nlike this are always fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.08,0:21:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so even though I'm 17,\NI really enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.42,0:21:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The treasure didn't\Nturn out to be those jewels,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.10,0:21:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was there, Dad. It was there--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--the real treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.37,0:23:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened shortly\Nafter you were born, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.50,0:23:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your old man's nearly-released\Nmanuscript was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.42,0:23:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.71,0:23:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.17,0:23:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it appeared to have\Nbeen one of his fans,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.09,0:23:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but neither the thief nor\Nthe manuscript was ever found.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.18,0:23:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's who the dead jewel\Nthief was who drew the other map...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.89,0:23:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He couldn't afford to\Nrelease it as it had been stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.61,0:23:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I never thought\Nit would turn up like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.99,0:23:40.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo Yusaku
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.04,0:23:48.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,To my son, Shinichi
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.50,0:24:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! Ran and the others are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.51,0:24:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why is he after Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.94,0:24:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Mountain Lodge Bandage\NMan Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.06,0:24:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.24,0:24:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sneak-a-peek.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.73,0:24:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is finally Part 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.92,0:24:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll identify the culprit in Part 1. Heh, heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.64,0:24:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
